{"article_id":"BFQf5HrJnFGURlEQ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court heard argument yesterday in Masterpiece Cakeshop v. Colorado Civil Rights Commission .","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"The issue is whether a conservative Christian baker","depth":12},{"id":2,"text":"who believes","depth":13},{"id":3,"text":"that weddings are inherently religious","depth":14},{"id":4,"text":"and that same-sex marriages are religiously prohibited","depth":14},{"id":5,"text":"can be required to design and create a cake","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"to celebrate the wedding of a same-sex couple .","depth":12},{"id":7,"text":"The case tests the nation ' s commitment to liberty and justice for all .","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"And we aren ' t doing well on the part about \" for all. \"","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"Too many Americans , left and right , religious and secular , want liberty for their own side in the culture wars , but not for the other side .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"The Supreme Court sometimes succumbs to these cultural divisions ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"but perhaps this time it will do better .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"In Obergefell v. Hodges ,","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"announcing the constitutional right to same-sex marriage ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"Justice Anthony Kennedy and the four liberals opened their opinion","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"by declaring ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"\" The Constitution promises liberty to all within its reach , \" a liberty","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"that allows persons \" to define and express their identity . \"","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"Masterpiece Cakeshop tests","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"whether they meant it .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Conservative believers are also within the Constitution ' s reach .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Does the Constitution protect their right","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"to define and express their identity in religious terms","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"equally with the right of same-sex couples","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to define and express their identity in sexual terms ?","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"It should .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"The two of us , in briefs and articles , have long urged judges , legislators , and our fellow citizens to protect the right of same-sex couples","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"to marry","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"and protect the right of religious dissenters","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"not to assist with those marriages .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"That does not mean undercutting nondiscrimination laws in most cases of commercial goods and services .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"The Court can recognize a carefully defined right in the case of Jack Phillips , the owner of Masterpiece Cakeshop ,","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"and make room for both sides in the culture wars .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"This is a unique event :","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"a wedding .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"That makes a difference .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"The wedding baker ' s job , like that of the caterer , florist , photographer , and bridal shop , is to make his part of the wedding the best and most memorable","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"it can be .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"He is promoting the wedding and the marriage","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"it celebrates .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Phillips , the owner of Masterpiece Cakeshop , says","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"he can not do that .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Many bakers may feel","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that their responsibility ends","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"when they deliver the cake .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"But Phillips feels morally responsible for what he creates","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"and helps to celebrate .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"The result is that Phillips no longer makes wedding cakes for anybody .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"He has surrendered 40 percent of his business","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and laid off half his employees .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Unless the Supreme Court intervenes ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"this is a permanent loss of occupation .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"His alternative was to permanently surrender his conscience .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"And to what end ?","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"To avoid the one-time offense to the same-sex couple","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"of being turned away","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"and being reminded of what they knew anyway :","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"that some Americans still disapprove of their relationship .","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"Their right","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"to be married","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"and to have a wedding cake","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"were never at issue .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"Many bakers were eager for their business ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"and","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"when the story broke ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"the couple promptly accepted an offer of a free wedding cake .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Same-sex couples and religious dissenters make parallel claims to liberty .","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"They each argue","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"that a core aspect of their identity is so fundamental","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"that it should be left to each individual , free of all nonessential regulation .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Their conduct can not be separated from their sexual orientation or their religious beliefs .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Believers can no more fail to act on their understanding of God 's will","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"than all gays and lesbians can remain celibate .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"They each seek to live out their identities in public as well as in private .","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"Same-sex couples are entitled to free access to the marketplace ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"but so are religious dissenters .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"The question is how to maximize access for both sides","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"without requiring either to surrender core elements of their identity .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Finally , both religious dissenters and same-sex couples are condemned by many other Americans .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"One side sees bigotry ;","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"the other side sees sin .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Blue states refuse to protect religious liberty ;","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"red states refuse to enact LGBTQ rights laws .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Most of the commentary on the case has focused on Phillips ' s free speech claim .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"But the Court can decide the case on narrower grounds under the Free Exercise Clause ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"as we urged in a friend-of-the-court brief .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"The free exercise claim is inherently limited to sincere religious objectors .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"And in this case , it is largely limited to weddings , a context","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that Phillips and many other believers understand as religious .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Phillips claims no right","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"to refuse service to gays and lesbians more generally .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Any merchant","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"who did so","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"would have a losing case .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"For","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"if merchants could discriminate anywhere and in any context ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"the obstacle to LGBTQ participation in the marketplace would be much greater ,","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"and the government ' s interest","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"in protecting them","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"would be much greater .","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"There may be religious conservatives","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"who argue for that ;","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Phillips and his responsible supporters do not .","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"Of course Phillips ' s opponents exaggerate his claim as much","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"as possible .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"They strain to analogize his case to Jim Crow restaurants","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"turning away black people ,","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"or a fundamentalist-owned bank","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"refusing to handle women ' s accounts .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"Courts would properly reject such ongoing denials of service","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"- and they did in the Jim Crow era .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"This case involves a wedding , an event","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"that we all hope to be the center of only once ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"even if things go badly ,","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"no more than a very few times .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"This is not the same as visiting a restaurant or bank","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"- it ' s a rare occasion .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"The free exercise claim has been neglected","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"because too many people have read too much into the Supreme Court ' s 1990 decision in Employment Division v. Smith .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"The Court said","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"that the Free Exercise Clause does not apply to laws","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"that are \" neutral and generally applicable. \"","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"So Oregon could apply its \" across-the-board criminal prohibition \"","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"to ban Native Americans from using peyote as their sacrament in worship services .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"Too many observers have casually assumed","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"that all but the most outrageous laws are neutral and generally applicable","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"- that the Free Exercise Clause now bars only laws","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"that single out religion for uniquely unfavorable regulation ,","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"or perhaps only laws","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"that stem from government hostility to the regulated religion .","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"But that is not what the Court said .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"The Court did not explicitly define \" neutral and generally applicable law. \"","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"But it gave examples , in Smith and in one later case , Church of the Lukumi Babalu Aye v. City of Hialeah ,","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"which involved animal sacrifice .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Read carefully ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"those cases say this :","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"If a law permits exceptions for some secular conduct","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"that is analogous to the regulated religious conduct ,","depth":16},{"id":139,"text":"then the state must also allow a religious exception ,","depth":16},{"id":140,"text":"or show a compelling reason why not .","depth":16},{"id":141,"text":"When the state exempts the secular conduct from regulation , but not the analogous religious conduct ,","depth":16},{"id":142,"text":"it is unjustly discriminating against religion .","depth":16},{"id":143,"text":"And that is what the Free Exercise Clause forbids .","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"The secular exceptions need not be broad , or numerous ,","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"to require a religious exception .","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"In Smith , the Court reaffirmed an earlier decision","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"requiring South Carolina to pay unemployment compensation to a woman","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"who lost her job","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"for refusing work on her Sabbath .","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"But South Carolina had a rule","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"that allowed unemployment compensation to be paid to workers","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"who refused work for \" good cause. \"","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"There weren ' t many \" good causes , \"","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"but the Court said","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"there were \" at least some. \"","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"You can refuse work in a strip club","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"even if there are openings ,","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"for example ,","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"and collect unemployment instead ;","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"you can decline a job","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"because of an unrealistically long commute .","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"The state ,","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"the Court concluded ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"had to put religious reasons","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"for refusing work","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"in the very small set of \" good \" reasons , and not in the vastly larger set of \" bad \" reasons .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"In Lukumi , the Court struck down the city of Hialeah ' s ban on religious sacrifice of animals .","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"In this case , there were many permitted secular reasons","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"for killing animals","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"( food , hunting , euthanasia , etc . ) ,","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"and only a few forbidden reasons .","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"But the Court again decided","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"that such tallying was not required ;","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"it said","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"the Hialeah ordinances did not come close to constitutionality .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"Florida law allowed the use of live rabbits","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"to train racing greyhounds .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"Comparing that state law to the city ' s ban on animal sacrifice ,","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"the Court said","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"that the law \" devalues religious reasons","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"for killing [ animals ]","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"by judging them to be of lesser import than nonreligious reasons . \"","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"Four federal courts of appeals and several other state and federal courts have recognized","depth":7},{"id":184,"text":"that granting even one or a few secular exceptions makes a law less than generally applicable","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"and requires a compelling justification","depth":9},{"id":186,"text":"for refusing religious exceptions .","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"The most prominent of these decisions ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"written by then-Judge Samuel Alito in 1999 , on the Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit ,","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"held","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"that a Muslim policeman","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"who wore a beard as a religious duty","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"could challenge the Newark Police Department ' s ban on facial hair .","depth":9},{"id":193,"text":"The department had granted a medical exception for officers with a skin condition","depth":9},{"id":194,"text":"aggravated by shaving .","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"That single exception ,","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"the court said ,","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"made the law non-generally applicable ,","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"triggering strict constitutional scrutiny ;","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"granting the medical exception","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"but denying the religious exception \" made a value judgment in favor of secular motivations , but not religious motivations . \"","depth":10},{"id":201,"text":"What the courts said","depth":5},{"id":202,"text":"when bakers refused to write anti-gay messages on their cakes","depth":5},{"id":203,"text":"How does all this apply to Masterpiece Cakeshop ?","depth":5},{"id":204,"text":"Colorado ' s public accommodations law prohibits businesses from discriminating on the basis of sexual orientation , religion , or other traditional civil rights categories .","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"On its face it has no secular exceptions .","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"But it has been unevenly enforced in practice .","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"The Colorado Court of Appeals ruled","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"that Phillips discriminated on the basis of sexual orientation","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"by refusing to create a cake","depth":13},{"id":210,"text":"celebrating a same-sex marriage","depth":13},{"id":211,"text":"- because that celebratory message is closely associated with gays and lesbians .","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"But it explicitly approved three cases","depth":11},{"id":213,"text":"holding","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"that other bakers did not discriminate on the basis of religion","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"when they refused to create cakes with a quotation from Leviticus","depth":15},{"id":216,"text":"condemning homosexuality","depth":15},{"id":217,"text":"- a message obviously associated with a certain set of religious believers .","depth":14},{"id":218,"text":"The Colorado regulations are clear","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"that religious discrimination includes not just discrimination","depth":14},{"id":220,"text":"based on affiliation ,","depth":14},{"id":221,"text":"but discrimination","depth":14},{"id":222,"text":"based on a particular religious belief -","depth":14},{"id":223,"text":"exactly what the other bakers did .","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"The appeals court said many more inconsistent things about the two sets of cases .","depth":9},{"id":225,"text":"It let the protected bakers take responsibility for the message","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"their cakes would send","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"and refuse to send that message .","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"By contrast , it denied","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"that Phillips ' s wedding cake would send any message ,","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"and then said","depth":14},{"id":231,"text":"that","depth":15},{"id":232,"text":"if his cake did send a message ,","depth":16},{"id":233,"text":"it would be the customers ' message , not the baker ' s .","depth":16},{"id":234,"text":"It said","depth":15},{"id":235,"text":"that the protected baker ' s willingness","depth":17},{"id":236,"text":"to make other cakes with \" Christian themes \" for other Christian customers","depth":17},{"id":237,"text":"was exonerating ,","depth":16},{"id":238,"text":"but that Phillips ' s willingness","depth":16},{"id":239,"text":"to make anything but a wedding cake for his gay and lesbian customers","depth":16},{"id":240,"text":"was irrelevant .","depth":15},{"id":241,"text":"Refusing to create a cake with a message","depth":16},{"id":242,"text":"associated with a protected class of customers","depth":17},{"id":243,"text":"- whether same-sex couples or conservative Christians -","depth":17},{"id":244,"text":"either discriminates against that class","depth":15},{"id":245,"text":"or it does not .","depth":14},{"id":246,"text":"The message on a cake is either the baker ' s message or the customer ' s message , or perhaps the message of both .","depth":13},{"id":247,"text":"But the answers to these questions can not vary","depth":14},{"id":248,"text":"depending on whether the state agrees with the message ,","depth":15},{"id":249,"text":"which is how it worked out in the Colorado courts .","depth":15},{"id":250,"text":"Protecting the bakers","depth":13},{"id":251,"text":"who refused to make the Leviticus cakes","depth":13},{"id":252,"text":"undermines the state ' s interest","depth":13},{"id":253,"text":"in eliminating religious discrimination","depth":13},{"id":254,"text":"at least as much","depth":12},{"id":255,"text":"as protecting Phillips would undermine the state ' s interest","depth":13},{"id":256,"text":"in eliminating sexual-orientation discrimination .","depth":13},{"id":257,"text":"The state has tried to distinguish the two sets of bakers","depth":13},{"id":258,"text":"by saying","depth":14},{"id":259,"text":"that the protected bakers would not make the Leviticus cake for anybody .","depth":14},{"id":260,"text":"The state court never made that argument .","depth":12},{"id":261,"text":"The protected bakers were in the business","depth":13},{"id":262,"text":"of making custom cakes with messages and designs","depth":14},{"id":263,"text":"requested by customers ,","depth":14},{"id":264,"text":"and they refused the Leviticus cake","depth":13},{"id":265,"text":"because they disapproved a message","depth":14},{"id":266,"text":"strongly associated with a particular religious view .","depth":14},{"id":267,"text":"Phillips is in the same business ,","depth":12},{"id":268,"text":"and refused for the same reason","depth":13},{"id":269,"text":"( substituting sexual orientation for religion ) .","depth":13},{"id":270,"text":"And suppose","depth":12},{"id":271,"text":"Phillips says","depth":13},{"id":272,"text":"he wouldn ' t make a cake with two grooms for anybody .","depth":13},{"id":273,"text":"The state ' s answers at yesterday ' s oral argument clearly implied","depth":10},{"id":274,"text":"that Colorado would say","depth":11},{"id":275,"text":"that ' s sexual orientation discrimination .","depth":11},{"id":276,"text":"We should not have to go through this detailed analysis","depth":8},{"id":277,"text":"to protect a simple act of conscience .","depth":8},{"id":278,"text":"Same-sex couples should be free to marry , with fancy weddings and wedding cakes ,","depth":9},{"id":279,"text":"and conscientious objectors should not be required to assist .","depth":9},{"id":280,"text":"But under the Supreme Court ' s interpretation , the Constitution protects religious conscience only against laws","depth":10},{"id":281,"text":"that fail its test of general applicability .","depth":10},{"id":282,"text":"Fortunately for Jack Phillips , the Colorado law","depth":11},{"id":283,"text":"as it was administered","depth":11},{"id":284,"text":"fails that test .","depth":10},{"id":285,"text":"Douglas Laycock is a professor of constitutional law at the University of Virginia .","depth":2},{"id":286,"text":"Thomas C. Berg is a professor of constitutional law at University of St. Thomas","depth":4},{"id":287,"text":"( Minnesota ) .","depth":4},{"id":288,"text":"They have long advocated","depth":5},{"id":289,"text":"for protecting same-sex marriage","depth":5},{"id":290,"text":"and for protecting religious dissenters .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":581,"left":575,"right":580,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":575,"left":373,"right":574,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":373,"left":356,"right":372,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":356,"left":321,"right":355,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":316,"right":320,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":316,"left":310,"right":315,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":310,"left":302,"right":309,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":300,"right":301,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":297,"right":299,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":0,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":294,"right":295,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":1,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":2,"right":292,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":295,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":7,"right":298,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":309,"left":307,"right":308,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":304,"right":306,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"paren